QUALIFICATION: as incrassatum Ström; [in Gray] The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 20: 269; Three nominal species were originally included in Hinia: Hinia minuta. Nassa. [Hinia] reticulata. [Hinia] laevigata. Planaxis mollis, Sow. The same three species were included in Hima [Leach, 1852, A synopsis of the Mollusca of Great Britain [MS work edited by Gray]: 122, 123], which is thus clearly an incorrect subsequent spelling. However, Cossmann [1901, Essais de paléoconchologie comparée, 4: 204, 210] treated Hinia and Hima as two different valid names. Woodring's [1928, Carnegie Institution of Washington, Publication 385: 265] type designation for Hima is ambiguous, but Marwick [1931, New Zealand Geological Survey Palaeontological Bulletin, 13: 115] designated Buccinum minutum Pennant, 1777, as type species of Hima. Invalid: junior objective synonym of Tritia, with the same type species. See also Hinea

QUALIFICATION: as Buccinum cuvierii Payraudeau, 1826; Original rank: subgenus (of Nassa). The type species fixation by Bucquoy, Dautzenberg & Dollfus is somewhat ambiguously worded (One can consider N[assa] costulata as the type of this subgenus), but it has generally been considered a valid fixation. Buccinum costulatum Brocchi, 1814, was not a nominal species originally included in Telasco, but Bucquoy et al. listed Buccinum variabile [an originally included species] in its synonymy. Cossmann, 1901, Essais de paléoconchologie comparée, 4: 212, also cited Buccinum costulatum Brocchi as neotype [= type species]
